Package si.ijs.kt.clus.data.rows

Class RowData

java.lang.Object
si.ijs.kt.clus.data.ClusData
si.ijs.kt.clus.data.rows.RowData
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, MSortable
public class RowData extends ClusData implements MSortable, Serializable
Multiple rows (tuples) of data. One row (DataTuple) is one instance of the data with target and description attributes.

    • sample

      public RowData sample(int N, ClusRandomNonstatic rnd)
      Create a random sample with replacement of this RowData. Uses the ClusRandom.RANDOM_SAMPLE random generator Be careful when using this method! Current use in FindBestTest is wrong in the case when N != 0: this is used for finding the best test. However, if N != 0 (otherwise we simply return all the data), this can lead to problems (duplicates of tuples --> wrong statistics --> ...) This is considered a small bug since usually N = 0, because the option SplitSampling in section [Tree] is usually not used.
      Parameters:
      N - The size of the random subset
      Returns:
      If N > 0: a new RowData containing the random sample of size N If N == 0: a copy of this RowData object (i.e. no sampling)
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if N < 0
